\end{equation}
We introduce the further notation in the plane of the quadrilateral
\begin{eqnarray}
&&{\vec {AB}}={\vec s}_I= (a,0), \qquad  {\vec {AC}}={\vec s}_J= (a',b),\\
&&{\vec {AC}}={\vec{ \bar{s}}}_I{\,}= (a',b), \qquad  {\vec {AD}}={\vec{\bar{ s}}}_J{}= (a'',b),
\end{eqnarray}
We only pay attention to the non-covariant contributions. To third order they just add up and we obtain
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{NCFGK3}
{\mathbf \Sigma}_{ABCA}^{(3)}+{\mathbf \Sigma}_{ACDA}^{(3)}&=&\frac {(a''-a'+a)}{12}
\Big\{3a'(a''-a) [\partial_1{\mathbf A}_1,{\mathbf A}_1] \nonumber\\
&+& b (a''+a'-a) \Big([\partial_1{\mathbf A}_1,{\mathbf A}_2]+[\partial_1{\mathbf A}_2,{\mathbf A}_1]+[\partial_2{\mathbf A}_1,{\mathbf A}_1] \Big)\nonumber \\
&&  +b^2\Big[[\partial_2{\mathbf A}_1,{\mathbf A}_2]+[\partial_2{\mathbf A}_2,{\mathbf A}_1]+[\partial_1{\mathbf A}_2,{\mathbf A}_2]\Big]\Big\}.
\end{eqnarray}
We see that the above is not zero in general. Nevertheless, in the  symmetrical case of  a
parallelepiped, characterized by the condition
\begin{equation}
