\end{equation}
the non-covariant piece (\ref{NCFGK3}) vanishes. Of course, the above condition includes that of a rectangle which is  $a=a'$ y   $ a''=0 $.

Nevertheless, the failure of the composition property of the calculational method in Ref. \cite{FGK} is illustrated at the fourth order where one should have a cancelation among each of the corresponding pieces $({\mathbf \Sigma}_{ABCA})_p^{(4)}$ and $ ({\mathbf \Sigma}_{ACDA})_p^{(4)}, \,\, p=2,3.$ The simplest symmetrical case corresponds to  ${\mathbf \Sigma}_2^{(4)}$ and leads to

\begin{eqnarray}
&&({\mathbf \Sigma}_{ABCA})_{2}^{(4)}+ ({\mathbf \Sigma}_{ACDA})_{2}^{(4)}=\frac{1}{4!}([A_J,(2x_I^2+x_J^2-2x_Ix_J)(A_I-A_J)+x_J^2A_I]\nonumber\\
&&+2[A_I,(x_I^2-x_Ix_J)A_J]+2[x_I(A_I-A_J),x_J(A_I-A_J)]-2[x_JA_I,x_IA_I] )\nonumber\\
&&\neq 0.
\end{eqnarray}

Where:
\begin{eqnarray}
A_I=s_I^aA_a, \qquad A_J=s_J^aA_a 
\end{eqnarray}





